 few weeks ago, Jason posted his thoughts on the changes in Safari in iOS 15. Since Apple released another beta with yet more changes,Â it seemed like a good time toÂ take a lookÂ at the comments people had to <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/350064/safari-ios-15-interface-address-bar-tab-groups-gestures-refresh.html\">Jasonâ€™s article.</a>Â </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>I actually really like the changes. So much easier to use one handed.</p>â€” j8s (@jason111001) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/jason111001/status/1410681133470203914?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 1, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>I for myself like it. On a phone most sites are opened from links, not you typing. And swiping between tabs used to be a pain, now it's a breeze. So just stop the whining. Also no home button. And it's not a monchrom LCD.</p>â€” Gergely Rozsnyai (@GergelyRozsnyai) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/GergelyRozsnyai/status/1410669350206554116?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 1, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>is Apple so hard up to make changes that they now make changes just for change sake???  have they lost creativity???   Steve Jobsâ€¦..where are YOUâ€¦Apple is in serious need of a CREATIVITY BOOSTâ€¦.TIM is not a tech guy.</p>â€” secret name (@dbfssecret) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/dbfssecret/status/1410668995175456768?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 1, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/ben-chapman-facebook.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/10159220711961544&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a></div>\n\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/dom-harness-facebook.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/10159220711961544&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a></div>\n\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/bencoatsworth-facebook.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/10159220711961544&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a></div>\n\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/dangriffiths-fabebook.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" /></figure><p>Facebook</p></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Your hot takes on the Touch Bar</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Roman recently <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/351326/macbook-pro-ditch-touch-bar-rumors-function-keys.html\">postedÂ his thoughts about the Touch Bar</a> on the MacBook Pro.Â Rumor says that it could go away when the 14- and 16-inch Apple silicon MacBook Pros are announced, and he wouldnâ€™t miss it. People have strong options about the Touch Bar.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Actually once you get used to it, itâ€™s pretty cool and practical. Never once thought itâ€™s useless since I started using it.</p>â€” sv (@seyhanvs) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/seyhanvs/status/1418251000138326017?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 22, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>I will miss it. I think removing it is truly a mistake.</p>â€” ğŸ˜ (@YesYepYeahYah) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/YesYepYeahYah/status/1418246610086105097?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 22, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Congrats moron, you talked them out of functionality and just for fun, weâ€™ll pay the same price.  Small minded, tech bloggers couldnâ€™t adjust their work flow.  Meanwhile the rest of us are like hey I used that!  I hope they turn the whole keyboard into a Touch Bar!</p>â€” Whoda (@Whodakat) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/Whodakat/status/1418423469641854979?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 23, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>I like the Touch Bar after begrudgingly buying a MacBook Pro w/ it.   Using it doesnâ€™t distract my focus like w/ Microsoftâ€™s Office Ribbon (still after a decade).   Maybe the authorâ€™s Touch Bar experience would have been better if not for being using a Mac Pro years ago</p>â€” Joseph T. (@TJisonline) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/TJisonline/status/1419258640431734784?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 25, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>The biggest issue is probably the lack of tactile feedback. A regular F1 key you can press blind. A touchbar one, you canâ€¦ if you are lucky.<br />Also, is it worth the added price? I'm not talking about real cost, but the price Apple charges for it.</p>â€” AvanCade (@AvanCadeNL) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/AvanCadeNL/status/1419530270533898240?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 26, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>To me the Touchbar was awkward to use. I already don't like the oversized trackpad, I am always having to repeatedly click one side or the other just to get clicking on a screen object to work. With the Touchbar I now had to arch my hand over the keyboard just to use it. A pain.</p>â€” ben_marko (@BobfromCT) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/BobfromCT/status/1419271256248098818?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 25, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/gerioneil-facebook.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/10159220711961544&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>A hot take on the Siri updates</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We ended this episode with theÂ <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/352142/ios-15-siri-third-party-app-integrations-deprecated.html\">news</a> thatÂ Apple is disablingÂ severalÂ different Siri interactions in iOS 15. For example, you wonâ€™t be able toÂ hail a ride throughÂ Uber or Lyft via Siri.Â One reader had this thought:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Siri actually does something? Since when? It's literally the worst \"digital assistant\" on the market. Apple should just remove it and the overhead it consumes on it's products and chalk it up to another failed venture like Apple Maps and their failed advertising platform.</p>â€” OpinionsRlikeBLEEP (@opinionslikeblp) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/opinionslikeblp/status/1420408256623697920?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 28, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><h2>How to subscribe to the Macworld Podcast</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can subscribe to the Macworld Podcastâ€”or leave us a review!â€”<a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/id563933198&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">right here in the Podcasts app</a>. Or you can point your favorite podcast-savvy RSS reader at: <code>http://feeds.soundcloud.com/users/58576458-macworld/tracks</code></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Macworld Podcast is also <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://open.spotify.com/show/3uyZkE4tjbwNNrJCLsBUAM?si=OdOljEAYQvC_ewEsMfKzXA&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">available on Spotify</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To find previous episodes, visit <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/opinion/podcast\">Macworldâ€™s podcast page</a> or our home on <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=http://www.soundcloud.com/macworld&amp;xcust=1-1-352235-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">Soundcloud</a>.</p>\n</div>","author":"Macworld Staff","siteTitle":"Macworld","siteHash":"37e84dd5a21fa961d6d6630e269546024dbb7741b2e2fadbe74f47383c70dfbb","entryHash":"204929ef7d4cb1554c5ce98455045d825485fa2a04a7db5c3de6085c52d292c0","category":"Apple"}